  "prompt": "How do I create hotspot for windows 10?",
  "response": "To create a mobile hotspot in Windows 10, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open Settings\n\u2022 Click the Start menu\n\u2022 Select \"Settings\" (gear icon)\n\n2. Go to Network & Internet\n\u2022 Click \"Network & Internet\" in the settings window\n\n3. Select Mobile Hotspot\n\u2022 Click on \"Mobile hotspot\" in the left sidebar\n\n4. Configure Hotspot\n\u2022 Toggle \"Share my internet connection with other devices\" to ON\n\u2022 Choose which internet connection you want to share (Wi-Fi or Ethernet)\n\u2022 Click \"Edit\" to change network name and password\n\n5. Alternative Method (Using Quick Settings)\n\u2022 Open Action Center (click notification icon in taskbar)\n\u2022 Find \"Mobile hotspot\" tile\n\u2022 Click to turn on\n\n6. Alternative Command Prompt Method\n\u2022 Open Command Prompt as administrator\n\u2022 Type: netsh wlan set hostednetwork mode=allow ssid=YourNetworkName key=YourPassword\n\u2022 Type: netsh wlan start hostednetwork\n\nRequirements:\n\u2022 Windows 10\n\u2022 Wi-Fi or Ethernet connection\n\u2022 Compatible wireless adapter\n\nNote: Data usage will depend on your mobile/internet plan.\n\nWould you like me to explain any step in more detail?",
